Supporters of the head of state demonstrated on Saturday.
In Israel, Ukrainian tourists are waiting for the Holy Land, the navel of the world and a sea of brine
The Promised Land combines the majesty of Bible truths with modern comforts and pristine nature.
"AIF" identified the five most important reasons why you should visit Israel.
Reverence in the Holy Land
The river Jordan where Jesus was baptized is worth visiting.
It is believed that anyone who enters this "baptism pool" will receive divine grace.
And Galilee, the site of Jesus' miracles: turning water into wine at the wedding, walking on water, calming the storm and the full nets.
In this very place, Jesus appeared to his disciples after his resurrection.
But the greatest number of holy sites is in Jerusalem.
Believers here follow the Via Crucis or the Way of the Cross of Jesus (in Latin "Via Dolorosa").
It begins at the Fortress of Antony, the Praetorium, where the trial took place, and continues through the streets of the Old City, to the Holy Sepulcher on Mount Golgotha, the place of the crucifixion, the Stone of the Unction and the burial place of Jesus.
In this same place is also the symbolic Christian World Ombligo, which symbolizes the salvation of humanity.
And the Holy Cross Monastery in Jerusalem, built on the site where, according to Christian legend, there was a tree from which the cross for the crucifixion of Jesus was made.
Jerusalem is also home to the holiest site in the Jewish world, the Western Wall, the remains of a temple destroyed by the Romans in 70 AD.
As is tradition, people of different religions leave here notes with their wishes, which will then be realized.
Take a vertical trip
The ruins of the Masada Fortress were what remained of a secret refuge from the enemies, which Herod the Great had built in 25 B.C. for his family.
They are found on mountain cliffs at an altitude of 450 m above sea level.
And to get there on your own, only those who are dedicated to climbing.
The rest of you can reach this historic summit by the funicular.
And in the north of the country at an altitude of 1600-2040 m is the famous ski resort Hermón, where in the winter months there is a great influx of tourists.
Bus services are available from the foot of the hill.
