From Friday night until sunset Saturday, markets and shops are closed and public transportation is disrupted.
But Sunday morning marks the beginning of a new work week.
Many cafes, restaurants, and hotels serve only kosher food, which excludes pork, shellfish, fish without scales, and dishes that combine milk and meat.
There is a wide selection of dishes made with beef and lamb, soups and desserts prepared with coconut milk, the traditional Hebrew cream called hummus, a wide variety of sauces, falafel, which are balls of ground garbanzo, fruits and vegetables.
