Then he sells it for 10,000 rupees (83 cents) to the petrochemical industry, since this mineral is widespread in daily life and is used to make matches, fireworks, cosmetics, dynamite and even to bleach sugar.
"We normally carry 70 kilos, so each trip costs us about R46,000", explains Anto, who usually carries three items a day.
